# Incident Assistant — Project Rules

You are working on **Incident Assistant**, a Java 21 / Spring Boot 3 AI demo project.

This project must follow **specification-driven development**.

## Core principles

1. Do not implement features before a spec exists.
2. Do not modify code before producing an implementation plan.
3. Do not expand the current phase scope without human approval.
4. Each phase must be fully tested before the next phase starts.
5. Prefer simple monolith design first; avoid premature microservices.
6. Keep future microservice boundaries in mind through clean modules and interfaces.
7. AI behavior must be safe, testable, and grounded in evidence.
8. The assistant must separate facts, assumptions, and recommendations.
9. RAG answers must cite sources.
10. MCP tools must be explicit, controlled, and testable.
11. No automatic remediation actions in early phases.
12. All external dependencies must be abstracted behind interfaces.
13. All LLM calls must be mockable in tests.
14. All generated code must include meaningful unit and integration tests.
15. Update specs and README when behavior changes.

## Before coding, always produce

- Summary of requested work
- Affected files
- Proposed implementation plan
- Test plan
- Risks and assumptions

## After coding, always provide

- What changed
- Tests added
- Commands to run
- Known limitations
- Whether the phase acceptance criteria are satisfied
